ant to the language team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2020-08-06T04:43:36Z", "updated_at": "2020-08-11T20:26:25Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I tried this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n// Ought to work fine but doesn't\r\nfn borrow_and_deref<T>(p: T) -> i32 where for<'a> &'a T: Deref<Target=i32> {\r\n    *&p\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: Successful typechecking\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: \r\n<img width=\"723\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/634666/89491662-c12c2100-d77d-11ea-990a-81123c62194b.png\">\r\n\r\nIf we invoke deref manually, rather than implicitly through syntax sugar everything works fine:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n// Works, so the issue is specifically at the intersection of syntax\r\n// sugar and the trait bound\r\nfn borrow_and_deref<T>(p: T) -> i32 where for<'a> &'a T: Deref<Target=i32> {\r\n    *(&p).deref()\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo this issue is specifically at the intersection of this kind of constraint and the syntax sugar.\r\n\r\n[Playground link](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=785a851a1f604669e37d9c74cf4c2d7f)\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/75208/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/75208/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}